Aisha Yesufu, co-convener of BringBackOurGirls, BBOG, advocacy group, has warned President Muhammadu Buhari against applying any form of force on peaceful protesters. Nigerian youth hit the streets on Monday in continuation of the protests against the brutality and extrajudicial killings by police. Osogbo, capital of Osun State and Lagos and Oyo States witnessed a second wave of the End SARS protest on Monday. DAILY POST reports that demonstrators have returned to Lekki Toll Plaza, the scene of the military shooting currently under probe. Following the development, President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday warned against violent protests in Nigeria. He said anyone who commits acts capable of disrupting peace and stability will be dealt with Also on Sunday, the police reiterated its ban on gatherings, warning that such might be hijacked by unscrupulous elements. And reacting to this, Aisha, tweeted, “You either allow citizens protest peacefully or they will protest violently. Seems Nigeria learnt nothing from its handling of Boko Haram.”